reviews.review_text:
Best sounding board of 3-29-90 Branford and the boys bring their "A" game! Jazz meets Dead with astounding results. This recording gets my vote as the best soundboard of all the 3-29-90's posted on the Archive. Simply amazing! For the best in latter-day Dead, listen to:
7-2-89  Foxboro
7-7-89  Giants
10-9-89 Hampton
3-29-90 Nassau

my favorite version (soundboard only) of this show I was going to say the Charlie Miller SBD was the one, but I guess this contains a slight fix to that otherwise identical one.  So this is my favorite of the straight soundboard mixes of this night.

Is This Really 90's Show? I am floored! This is a simply outstanding show... especially from Estimated through The Wheel. This is some of the most experimental, hard jazz material I've ever heard from the Dead... and I've been listening since 1976. Aside from Jerry's voice being a wee bit rough (and a lower pitch than when he was younger), this show could easily have come from the early 70's... except that it has this tenacious, driving drone through music... especially Eyes. This one is a must!

And BTW - The sound is flipping phenomenal... thank you!
